title: Outback women leading way for land management
text:
Outback women leading way for land ma... Outback women leading way for land management Next Story Prev Story 53 min ago Read more: ABC News 
Janet Brooks has watched the slow progress on issues facing women in the outback - from feral animals to gender politics and the tyranny of distance. She lives with her husband, Anthony, and their four children on Cordillo Downs, an 8000 square kilometre cattle station in the far north east of South Australia.   ABC News.
